The paper discusses the evolution of operating systems in the context of heterogeneous compute engines, which falls under the category of operating systems (cs.OS). The paper also proposes the use of a database management system for operating system functions, which relates to the category of databases (cs.DB). The paper discusses the mathematical properties of the proposed system, which relates to the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses simulations of the proposed system, which relates to the category of performance (cs.PF). Finally, the paper discusses the potential implementation of the proposed system on different platforms, which relates to the category of architecture (cs.AR).
